The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Thursday, August 29, 2002 				 Lazard India gets new head
 OUR BUREAU																								New Delhi, Aug. 28: Ashish Guha has been appointed as chief executive of Lazard India.																								Guha is one of the five partners of Lazard India. He will now co-ordinate Lazard Indias activities and will report to chairman Udayan Bose who has relocated to London. 																								Lazard India is a 50:50 joint venture between Lazard Worldwide and Udayan Bose. It is active in corporate finance (mergers and acquisitions), privatisation and restructuring.																								The company is working with the disinvestment ministry for the privatisation of ITDC and the Shipping Corporation of India. It is also the advisor in MRPLs financial restructuring exercise.
